HEADWORD: Chiltern Hundreds
<hw>Chiltern Hundreds</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[<ets>AS</ets>.
<ets>Chiltern</ets> the Chiltern, high hills in Buckinghamshire, perh.
Fr. <ets>ceald</ets> cold + <ets>ern</ets>, <ets>⟦ae⟧rn</ets>,
place.]</ety> <def>A tract of crown land in Buckinghamshire and
Oxfordshire, England, to which is attached the nominal office of
steward. As members of Parliament cannot resign, when they wish to go
out they accept this stewardship, which legally vacates their
seats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

